title: LOVE - The Norse-Anglo-Saxon history of SEX
description:
This book is a quest of the origin of the English language. It is impossible to understand the development of the English language nor the Anglo-Saxon culture without including sex. Sex and curiosity are the two main drives that developed mankind.

The time-setting is the Bronze Age, when, in Northern Europe, the temperature was about 2-4 degrees warmer per day than today.
